# MODULE 1: JAVA FOUNDATIONS
## *"Understanding the Language Before Speaking It"*

---

## 1.1 What Is Java?

Java is a **high-level, class-based, object-oriented programming language**
designed with the philosophy:

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════╗
║   "Write Once, Run Anywhere"         ║
║         — Java's Core Promise        ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════╝
```

### The Java Ecosystem at a Glance:

| Component | Role |
|-----------|------|
| **JDK** (Java Development Kit) | Tools to write and compile Java |
| **JRE** (Java Runtime Environment) | Tools to run Java programs |
| **JVM** (Java Virtual Machine) | Executes bytecode on any platform |
| **Bytecode** | Intermediate compiled code (.class files) |

### How Java Code Runs:

```
  Your Code (.java)
        │
        ▼
   [ Compiler (javac) ]
        │
        ▼
   Bytecode (.class)
        │
        ▼
   [ JVM interprets ]
        │
        ▼
   Program Executes on ANY OS
```

---

## 1.2 Your First Java Program

```java
// File: HelloWorld.java
// Every Java program starts with a class definition

public class HelloWorld {

    // The main method — entry point of every Java application
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Print a message to the console
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
        System.out.println("Welcome to Java Programming!");

        // Print without newline
        System.out.print("Java is ");
        System.out.print("powerful.\n");

        // Formatted output
        System.out.printf("Version: %d, Language: %s%n", 17, "Java");
    }
}
```

### Output:
```
Hello, World!
Welcome to Java Programming!
Java is powerful.
Version: 17, Language: Java
```

### Breaking It Down:

```
public class HelloWorld     → Class declaration (must match filename)
    │
    └── public              → Accessible from anywhere
    └── class               → Keyword to define a class
    └── HelloWorld          → Class name (PascalCase convention)

public static void main(String[] args)
    │
    └── public              → Accessible by JVM
    └── static              → No object needed to call it
    └── void                → Returns nothing
    └── main                → Special method name JVM looks for
    └── String[] args       → Command-line arguments
```

